Trump wine, Trump ice.

24:28.266 --> 24:31.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
All this is money from the
campaign that eventually
goes to fatten the
wallets of Trump, Inc.

24:34.766 --> 24:39.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I don't know of anything illegal
about having a campaign do
a campaign visit at your own

24:42.800 --> 24:45.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
owned facility, as long
as it's arms-length.

24:45.166 --> 24:47.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But I think, from an appearance
standpoint, it's not great.

24:47.966 --> 24:52.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: The reelection
campaign spent more
than $6.3 million in
the first three months

24:53.566 --> 24:56.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of the year.

24:56.200 --> 24:59.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
More than $450,000 of that
went to Trump businesses,
including rent at the
Trump Tower in New York

25:01.633 --> 25:06.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and Trump hotels in New York
and Las Vegas, catering from
Trump restaurants, and thousands

25:07.366 --> 25:09.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of dollars for
Trump bottled water.

25:09.700 --> 25:14.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Critics say holding campaign
events at Trump properties
