running for president appears

26:03.566 --> 26:08.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to be trying to rewrite the
book on running for reelection.

26:08.033 --> 26:13.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
John Yang in Washington.

26:15.233 --> 26:19.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: As we
reported earlier, governments
and industries the
world over are trying to

26:25.966 --> 26:29.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
deal with effects of the latest
in a series of cyber-attacks.

26:29.966 --> 26:34.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The so-called ransomware
assault is the second such
strike in the last six weeks.

26:36.133 --> 26:38.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Hari Sreenivasan in
New York has more.

26:38.600 --> 26:42.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: This
attack originated yesterday
in Ukraine, and rapidly
spread through Europe

26:43.166 --> 26:45.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and beyond.

26:45.233 --> 26:48.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The virus is called
Petya, and it takes
over infected computers,
effectively locking out

26:49.233 --> 26:50.766 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
users.

26:50.766 --> 26:53.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
A payment is required to return
control of the machine and data.

26:53.433 --> 26:58.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In early May, a similar
virus called WannaCry spread
to over 150 countries.

27:00.933 --> 27:04.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This new attack shows
signs of greater technical
sophistication, but
both apparently used,

27:05.966 --> 27:09.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in part, a tool developed by the
U.S. National Security Agency,
a tool that was leaked into

27:09.733 --> 27:11.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the open last year.

27:11.766 --> 27:13.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
With me now for more on
this is Rodney Joffe.

27:13.866 --> 27:18.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He is the senior vice president
and national security executive
for Neustar, a cyber-security

27:18.800 --> 27:20.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
firm.

27:20.866 --> 27:24.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Rodney, it seems that we have
not learned that much from
what happened two months ago,

27:25.933 --> 27:28.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
but it seems that the attackers
have learned a little bit more.

27:28.500 --> 27:29.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RODNEY JOFFE, Senior
Vice President and Senior
Technologist, Neustar,
Inc.: There's no question

27:29.600 --> 27:31.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that this is more sophisticated.

27:31.666 --> 27:35.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When we look at the code, when
we look at the mechanism that
was used, this one is much

27:35.800 --> 27:37.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
more sophisticated.

27:37.266 --> 27:40.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It actually uses three different
vectors we have seen so far.

27:40.400 --> 27:45.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The vector you're talking about
that was used in WannaCry is
the third option that is used

27:46.166 --> 27:48.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
by this one.

27:48.233 --> 27:52.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It uses two others, but
the damage is much more
significant in this case.

27:54.166 --> 27:58.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is not looking like so much
like ransomware anymore, but
it's starting to look like it's

27:59.500 --> 28:03.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a deliberate attempt to cause
havoc by destroying machines.

28:03.033 --> 28:08.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Is
this something that a
hacker collective would
do, or is this something

28:10.000 --> 28:12.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
that a state government
would be interested in
doing, destabilizing
Ukraine from all of

28:12.866 --> 28:15.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
these companies that do business
with it or pay taxes to it?

28:15.866 --> 28:20.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
RODNEY JOFFE: You know,
it's real tough these
days to tell where the
dividing line is between

28:22.733 --> 28:24.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the criminals and nation
states, and they really do work
hand in hand, especially in

28:24.933 --> 28:27.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Eastern Europe.

28:27.000 --> 28:31.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But if you look this, the
criminals are obviously out
there for financial gain.

28:31.100 --> 28:36.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This was set up in such a way
that there's very little chance
of much in terms of financial

28:36.566 --> 28:38.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
gain.

28:38.600 --> 28:42.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think, as of last evening,
by the way, there was $10,500
that had actually paid into this

28:43.566 --> 28:45.666 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
wallet.

28:45.666 --> 28:47.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And I have got to tell
you that the effort that
went into writing the
code and distributing

28:47.266 --> 28:50.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
it clearly cost a lot
more than $10,500.

28:50.466 --> 28:55.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: What
is the measurable impact
on Ukraine going forward?

28:57.500 --> 29:01.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RODNEY JOFFE: I think that the
biggest problem that they're
going to be facing is the fact

29:02.666 --> 29:06.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that the ability to pay taxes to
the state is seriously affected.

29:06.100 --> 29:11.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We have seen images that
were tweeted of things
like supermarkets where
the checkout systems

29:13.333 --> 29:16.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
had been compromised -- and
we're showing the screen.

29:16.666 --> 29:21.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We also see the very large --
obviously, the multinational
shipping line that has now been

29:22.266 --> 29:24.400 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
affected.

29:24.400 --> 29:27.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it looks like a deliberate
attempt to cause some kind of
significant financial impact,

29:29.333 --> 29:32.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
not just on the citizens of
Ukraine, but on Ukraine itself.

29:32.866 --> 29:36.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: You
know, when you said
you noticed differences
in the design between

29:36.533 --> 29:41.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the WannaCry and this, do we
have any indication that paying
these people off actually gets

29:41.266 --> 29:44.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
you your data back, or was it
not even designed to do that?

29:44.066 --> 29:49.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RODNEY JOFFE: Theoretically,
it was designed to do that,
but it's clear so far that the

29:51.100 --> 29:54.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
mechanism that was put in place
to actually collect ransom is
nowhere near the sophistication

29:57.400 --> 29:59.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of the malware itself.

29:59.366 --> 30:02.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And you don't think that someone
would have made that kind
of mistake, built something

30:02.766 --> 30:07.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that was very, very effective
to compromise, and no
real ability to collect.

30:09.433 --> 30:13.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We haven't seen or heard
of anyone so far who has
been able to decrypt it.

30:15.300 --> 30:18.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And what we also know is that,
within a very short time after
the malware was discovered,

30:20.266 --> 30:23.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the single e-mail address
that was needed to communicate
with was actually shut down

30:23.666 --> 30:25.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
by the provider.

30:25.733 --> 30:30.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So that's one reason that I
believe that no one is going
to be able to easily get their

30:30.933 --> 30:33.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
data back.

30:33.000 --> 30:35.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The second thing is that there
are reports that are surfacing
now, as folks have looked

30:35.900 --> 30:40.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at the code, that there is
at least one bug in the code
that actually makes it so that

30:41.800 --> 30:43.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
decryption is not possible.

30:43.900 --> 30:47.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Are the rest
of us basically collateral
damage when it comes to what's

30:47.233 --> 30:49.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
happening, say, between
Ukraine and Russia?

30:49.133 --> 30:52.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is falling on the
day now where this is
Constitution Day for Ukraine.

30:52.900 --> 30:55.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They're celebrating their
independence from Russia,
what, 21 years ago.

30:55.533 --> 30:57.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
RODNEY JOFFE: We clearly
are collateral damage.

30:57.633 --> 31:01.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This was obviously
targeted at Ukraine.

31:01.933 --> 31:04.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
