42:01.533 --> 42:03.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
them and fighting them
and causing symptoms of
inflammation and infection.

42:03.666 --> 42:08.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MILES O'BRIEN: Could the
Lyme disease bacteria,
Borrelia burgdorferi, be
cleverly hiding inside

42:09.466 --> 42:11.466 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the human body?

42:11.466 --> 42:16.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Doctors cannot detect the
organisms using existing blood
tests, but Dr. Hu hopes Borrelia

42:17.333 --> 42:19.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and ticks are like
magnet and steel.

42:19.766 --> 42:21.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

42:21.900 --> 42:25.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LINDEN HU: The bacteria are so
well-adapted to their natural
vector, the tick, that they're

42:25.466 --> 42:29.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
