46:52.466 --> 46:55.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But did this mass
killing really happen?

46:55.033 --> 46:57.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And, if so, who were
the perpetrators?

46:57.433 --> 47:02.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Those questions must be decided
at the International Criminal
Court in the Netherlands.

47:02.133 --> 47:06.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's the setting for a new legal
thriller titled "Testimony"
and a new setting for acclaimed

47:06.766 --> 47:11.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
author Scott Turow, the attorney
and writer whose work has sold
more than 30 million copies

47:12.933 --> 47:15.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
since his debut novel,
"Presumed Innocent."

47:15.066 --> 47:18.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm not going to name all the
other bestsellers, Scott, but
it's nice to talk to you here.

47:18.133 --> 47:20.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
SCOTT TUROW, Author,
"Testimony": Jeff, it's
nice to talk to you.

47:20.666 --> 47:24.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You have
left behind the fictional
Kindle County, the
setting that many of us

47:24.233 --> 47:27.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are familiar with, that place
that's sort of familiar,
for a much broader palette.

47:27.633 --> 47:28.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT TUROW: Right.

47:28.633 --> 47:30.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Why?

47:30.800 --> 47:33.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT TUROW: You know, I
just sort of accumulated
a writer's bucket list,
and one of the things,

47:33.400 --> 47:37.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
years ago, that I decided I
would write about at some point
is the International Criminal

47:37.800 --> 47:41.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Court and The Hague,
just because I had never
read anything set there.

47:41.166 --> 47:43.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So you started
with the idea of the court.

47:43.700 --> 47:45.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SCOTT TUROW: I did, for sure.

47:45.333 --> 47:47.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Something
intrigued you about
those kinds of trials?

47:47.400 --> 47:51.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SCOTT TUROW: I had been in The
Hague in the year 2000, and
had found myself at a party

47:53.166 --> 47:56.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
surrounded by a bunch
of American lawyers
who were saying, you
have got to write about

47:56.100 --> 47:58.066 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this place.

47:58.066 --> 48:02.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And unlike most times when
people have ideas about Aunt
Tilly's watch or their divorce,

48:04.566 --> 48:07.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
this sounded like it
would actually make an
interesting setting.

48:07.466 --> 48:10.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: You have
the legal background,
and you're an attorney.

48:10.533 --> 48:14.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
How much research goes
into all of these -- the
stories that you write?

48:14.133 --> 48:15.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT TUROW: A lot.

48:15.833 --> 48:19.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I'm a year off my usual
cycle, because I went to
the Netherlands twice.

48:19.633 --> 48:22.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I went to Bosnia once.

48:22.533 --> 48:27.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I had a lot to learn about
first the court, even more to
learn about the Roma people,

48:30.700 --> 48:35.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and, of course, the Bosnian
conflict, about which I
was inexcusably ignorant.

48:37.300 --> 48:40.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, this
is set in the aftermath
of the Bosnian War.

48:40.000 --> 48:41.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT TUROW: Right.

48:41.966 --> 48:44.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: It's
about a group of Roma,
often known as gypsies...

48:44.000 --> 48:45.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT TUROW: Right.

48:45.466 --> 48:46.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: ... who
are still living there...

48:46.266 --> 48:47.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT TUROW: Right.

48:47.500 --> 48:48.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: ...
but resettled there.

48:48.300 --> 48:50.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT TUROW: Yes.

48:50.733 --> 48:54.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Resettled in the
fictional world, resettled
after the Bosnian War,
driven out of Kosovo,

48:56.966 --> 49:01.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and have chosen to live right
near the American NATO bases
in Bosnia, which were there for

49:04.733 --> 49:07.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a decade after the war to
sort of keep the peace.

49:07.433 --> 49:09.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: So you
have this big story.

49:09.100 --> 49:10.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You have this history.

49:10.733 --> 49:13.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But the way in, as always,
is a particular character.

49:13.933 --> 49:15.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT TUROW: Right.

49:15.466 --> 49:17.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: In this case,
a lawyer from Kindle County.

49:17.866 --> 49:18.866 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SCOTT TUROW: From Kindle County.

49:18.866 --> 49:20.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

49:20.366 --> 49:21.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SCOTT TUROW: The former U.S.
attorney in Kindle County.

49:21.900 --> 49:23.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: A very successful
man, who - - but is unfulfilled.

49:23.666 --> 49:25.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT TUROW: Right.

49:25.733 --> 49:29.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Thrown his life up for grabs,
says that he has never felt
fully at home with himself.

49:31.733 --> 49:36.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that helps explain why
he'd be willing to leave the
United States to work overseas.

49:38.033 --> 49:40.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And is that
the way in for you, really?

49:40.133 --> 49:44.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SCOTT TUROW: What interested
me was when I found that the
United States Congress had

49:44.700 --> 49:49.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
passed a law called the U.S.
Service-Members Protection Act,
which says that the president

49:52.166 --> 49:55.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
has authority to forcibly
rescue anybody -- any
American serviceman charged
before the International

49:58.000 --> 49:59.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Criminal Court.

49:59.500 --> 50:03.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, of course, the novelist
says, ah, good, conflict.

50:03.933 --> 50:08.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so the idea of an American
prosecutor investigating,
among other suspects, American

50:11.333 --> 50:15.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
service members was
immediately interesting.

50:15.233 --> 50:19.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: We can't go into
all the details of this plot
here, but, I mean, it's fair

50:19.533 --> 50:24.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to say that the book continues
what I think I can call your
own complicated relationship

50:26.033 --> 50:27.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to the law?

50:27.033 --> 50:29.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SCOTT TUROW: Yes, I think so.

50:29.100 --> 50:31.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You know, as a
kind of a both noble calling,
but also the -- what's the

50:31.866 --> 50:35.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
word, a tawdriness, in
some ways of the law.

50:35.033 --> 50:37.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT TUROW: Right.

50:37.033 --> 50:41.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There cannot be any greater
challenge to the law than
trying to adjudicate mass crimes

50:43.866 --> 50:44.866 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
like war crimes.

50:44.866 --> 50:47.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

50:47.000 --> 50:49.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I keep thinking, in your work
and in this one, that most of
us look at the legal system

50:49.800 --> 50:52.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
as a way to get at the truth.

50:52.066 --> 50:57.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Do you think of it as that,
or as a way to get at a truth,
or what's going on there,

50:59.533 --> 51:02.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
and what is it that
helps translates for
you as a novelist?

51:02.333 --> 51:07.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SCOTT TUROW: Well, you know,
I really think of the trial
of a lawsuit as an exercise in

51:07.066 --> 51:09.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
history.

51:09.100 --> 51:13.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And people are offering
competing visions of what
happened in the past.

51:15.500 --> 51:19.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the justice system
is willing to accept
either of those competing
visions and to impose

51:23.800 --> 51:26.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
consequences as a result.

51:26.533 --> 51:30.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When you think of it that way,
it's a little bit startling,
because we want to believe

51:30.300 --> 51:35.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that there is one truth and,
therefore, one justice, whereas,
if you have practiced law

51:37.266 --> 51:41.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as long as I have, you realize
that there is actually a
range of acceptable outcomes.

51:41.733 --> 51:43.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

51:43.233 --> 51:44.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Of course, truth these days
is a kind of fraught concept.

